 :tx/rationale "COMPILE-TO-PROMPT — PROBLEM: braid seed currently performs information RETRIEVAL (select relevant entities, format as text, stuff into budget). But the consumer is an LLM with a specific activation geometry, not a search engine user. The seed should perform COMPILATION: given task T and model state S, compute the minimal prompt transformation P such that LLM(S+P) produces optimal output for T. The store has 305 observations (128 design decisions, 28 theorems), 437 spec elements, 402 closed tasks with completion reasons, R(t) routing with 6-metric impact scores, M(t) telemetry with drift patterns. A compiler doesn't ask 'what's relevant?' — it asks 'what activation state does the model need?' These are fundamentally different questions. The four-field prompt structure: Priors (activate formal systems), Constraints (invariants this task must satisfy), Demonstrations (worked examples from closed tasks), Directives (task + acceptance criteria). This is the self-improvement loop from SEED.md S7 applied to the prompt itself."
